    "description": "In 1938 the previous ruler of Arachnos, The Weaver, plotted the death of Stefan Richter, the man who would later become known as Lord Recluse. This plot involved a young blind girl, Marlene Fortunata, who was to be used to lure the American mercenary into a trap. Marlene used her blindness to pretend not to be scared of Recluse’s horrid appearance. It took months for the plan to work, but eventually Marlene was ready to strike.<br><br>But fate is a fickle thing, and during this time the would-be assassin had actually fallen in love with Recluse. She revealed The Weaver's treachery, and the two hatched a bloody scheme.<br><br>That night, Lia went to The Weaver’s bed and gave him Recluse’s bloody helm. He was dead, she claimed, as she ran her fingers through The Weaver’s hair. Lia took the head of Arachnos to bed, and there used Recluse’s own poison to murder her former master. From then on, she had become the <i>'Vedova Rossa'</i>—the Red Widow.",
